Russian President Vladimir Putin signed a law establishing administrative responsibility for violations of the terms and conditions of payment of goods (work, services) in procurement for public and municipal purposes.
This law is designed to address the very acute problem of failing to meet its obligations to the contracting authorities in public and municipal procurement.
Two years ago, the situation in which entrepreneurs were unable to obtain payment under existing public and municipal contracts was widespread.
At the same time, the President of Russia commissioned the Office of the Attorney General of the Russian Federation to take the issue for special control.
Because the businessmen themselves could not deal with unconscionable customers who had entered into unfunded contracts, tried to evade their payment obligations and included illegal conditions in the contracts.
The problem was systemic as a whole in the country.
Since 2015, 9.7 thousand submissions have been made to the Public Prosecutor ' s Office in order to protect the rights of entrepreneurs, as a result of which 4.5 thousand officials have been involved in disciplinary proceedings, 533 administrative officials have been brought to the Investigative Offices for the purpose of conducting the examinations, and 46 criminal cases have been brought.
As a result, more than 66 billion roubles were owed to entrepreneurs.
These huge amounts, however, were not accumulated as a result of the non-payment of multi-billion-dollar contracts.
Many, systematic delays in the payment of services to entrepreneurs have resulted in more modest amounts.
Here's a typical case.
The manager of a small company won a multi-million roubles competition for social services.
The man had invested all his negotiable funds, had fully fulfilled his obligations, but had not received the money in time.
The result is an increasing financial sum of wages, taxes, loans that would result in bankruptcy if the business did not seek assistance from the Public Prosecutor ' s Office.
The problem has now been eliminated as far as possible in a number of regions.
However, as at the first half of 2017, the total debt of public and municipal contracts identified by the prosecutors of the Russian Federation entities was approximately 27.4 billion roubles.
In regions where debt ratios continue to reach critical levels, the Public Prosecutor ' s Office operates in manual anti-crisis management.
The Attorney-General personally conducts visiting meetings with representatives of the local authorities, where all violations revealed by prosecutors are thoroughly addressed and immediate remedial measures are taken.
Such operational meetings have already taken place in Jaroslav and Yekaterinburg this year.
The implementation of Federal Law No. 189-FZ on Amendments to the Code of Administrative Offences on Administrative Offences for the Establishment of Administrative Liability of Customer Officials for Violations of the Time and Procedure for the Payment of Goods (Working, Services) in Procurement for Public and Municipal Needs, signed last week by the President of Russia, will improve the payment discipline of public clients.
The draft law was drafted by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia at the initiative of the Henprocuratorate.
The new law will supplement the Code of Administrative Offences of the Russian Federation, which provides for a fine of 30,000 to 50,000 rubles for violation by the official of the employer of the time and manner in which goods, works and services are paid in public and municipal procurement.
If an official has already been sentenced to administrative punishment for a similar offence, he will be disqualified for a period of one to two years.
All prosecutors of the Russian Federation have already been instructed to ensure that these legislative novels are applied in practice.
