Ukraine offered to send Russians to prison for illegal crossing of the border
The Supreme Council of Ukraine has a draft law that criminalizes Russians for illegally crossing the Ukrainian border.
According to the RT channel, the document registered in the Ukrainian Parliament ' s electronic database entails three years ' imprisonment for Russian citizens who attempt to enter the country illegally.
It is noted that for a repeat offence or an act committed by a group of persons, the term of imprisonment may be increased to five years.
If the offender was detained at the border with weapons, the time of detention would increase to eight years.
