In Russia, there will be two new territories of pre-eminent socio-economic development - the Base and the Novotrowick.
The relevant decrees of the Government of the Russian Federation will enter into force today, 4 August.
The boundaries and economic activities of TOR in the territory of the city of Abaz in the Republic of Khakasia are defined.
In a town where 15,000 people live, there will be a special legal regime for entrepreneurship, as well as a minimum of resident capital investment, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
This is expected to attract some 2.5 billion rubles of investment into the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
The list of economic activities in which special legal arrangements for entrepreneurship will be in force in TOR “Abase” include, for example, plantation, livestock production, food production, soft drinks and clothing.
Already, the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements for the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the Territory on the urban enterprise Abacan Mine.
In January 2017, authorities in the region reported that Hakasia had met all the conditions of Mineconomy for the creation of TOR.
Similarly, the authorities of the Orenburg region have done the same.
There, the city of Novotroitsk will also establish an area of pre-eminent socio-economic development.
This will diversify the monogeneous economy, reduce its dependence on the urban enterprise AO Ural Steel, and create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of economic activities in which a special legal regime for entrepreneurs will operate in the new TOR includes, inter alia, freshwater fisheries, food production, medicines and medical supplies.
Novotroick became the first of the monogeneouss of the Orenburg region to be granted TOR status.
It will be recalled that the pre-development area is an economic zone with concessional tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges that are created to attract investment in improving the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for the residents of TOR are the following: income tax of no more than 5 per cent in the first five years, and not less than 10 per cent in the next five years, social contributions of 7.6 per cent in the 10 years, the use of the free customs zone, the concessional regime of connection to various infrastructure facilities, and the concessional rates of rent.
